results.name: Irregular array read by rows: The n-th row contains those distinct positive integers that each, when written in binary, occurs as a substring in binary n.
comment: This is sequence A119709 with the 0's removed.
The n-th row of this sequence contains A122953(n) terms.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Rows n = 1..512 of table, flattened
example: 6 in binary is 110. The distinct positive integers that occur as substrings in n when they and n are written in binary are: 1 (1 in binary), 2 (10 in binary), 3 (11 in binary), and 6 (110 in binary). So row 6 is (1,2,3,6).
